"""
Binade-Aligned Cancellation Lattice (BACL) — Invariant Audit.

Tests a candidate IEEE 754 geometric invariant:
  For positive normal-range floats a, b in IEEE 754 binary format,
  if floor_binade(a) >= floor_binade(b), then (a - b) is an integer
  multiple of ulp(b).

The c2 lattice theorem reduces to BACL applied to the (V_2, f_float) pair
under Conjecture C. BACL is the stripped-down geometric content.

Preregistry: Build_Docs/Reports/bacl_invariant_audit/preregistry.md
"""
