        ],
        "candidate_prior_names_searched": [
            "exact difference theorem",
            "binade-floor lemma",
            "cancellation lattice property",
            "integer-ulp invariant",
            "binade-aligned subtraction",
        ],
        "assessment": (
            "BACL-S is a direct corollary of IEEE 754 binade spacing — a "
            "folklore fact that is implicit in many error-analysis proofs "
            "but I do not find it stated as a named lemma with this exact "
            "form. Sterbenz's lemma is related but distinct (exactness vs "
            "lattice). Error-free transforms (TwoSum, Dekker) use BACL "
            "implicitly when establishing exact representability of "
            "residuals. The novelty in V4 is the USE of BACL as a substrate "
